---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro'
---

<ProjectLayout
  badge="Competitive Robotics · October 2025"
  title="LARC 2025 — Tec de Monterrey. The Tracky Project."
  description="Built and raced a custom ESP32-C6 line-follower robot that recovers from 90° turns in milliseconds — engineered under real competition pressure at LARC 2025."
  coverImage="/portfolio/images/larc_arena.webp"
  coverAlt="Tracky robot racing at LARC 2025 arena, Tec de Monterrey"
  ogImage="https://alesso-24.github.io/portfolio/images/larc_arena.webp"
  meta={[
    { label: 'Role',     value: 'Hardware Lead & Software Co-Dev' },
    { label: 'Venue',    value: 'Tec de Monterrey, N.L., Mexico' },
    { label: 'Event',    value: 'LARC 2025 — TIR Line Follower' },
    { label: 'Hardware', value: 'ESP32-C6 · IR Array · TB6612FNG' },
    { label: 'Software', value: 'C++ · PID Control · Python · BLE' },
  ]}
  githubHref="https://github.com/Alesso-24/Tracky"
  githubLabel="View Tracky on GitHub"
>

  <!-- Pull quote -->
  <blockquote class="pull-quote" data-reveal>
    <p>"Real engineering under fire — where theoretical math meets physical reality, and your code either holds the line or crashes out."</p>
  </blockquote>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- Demo Video -->
  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>Watch Tracky Race.</h2>
  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    One competition heat. A robot that has to think faster than the track curves.
    Watch the Inertial Recovery protocol activate on the 90° corners in real-time.
  </p>

  <div data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100" class="video-embed">
    <iframe
      src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/LlpaLHTaqiQ"
      title="Tracky LARC 2025 — Line Follower Race Demo"
      allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
      allowfullscreen
      loading="lazy"
    ></iframe>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>The Competition Experience.</h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    At the 25th Latin American Robotics Competition (LARC) in Nuevo León, we put our engineering
    to the ultimate test — facing top universities across Latin America in the TIR
    Line Follower category. Every millisecond counted, every heat was final.
  </p>
  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100">
    The environment was intense: the smell of fresh solder, high-pitch servo whines, teams
    pushing hardware to the breaking point. We were debugging C++ memory leaks on the fly,
    fighting BLE interference from neighboring robots, and constantly recalibrating
    IR arrays against the arena's shifting ambient light.
  </p>

  <div data-reveal data-reveal-delay="140" style="border-radius:18px; overflow:hidden; margin: clamp(28px,4vh,48px) 0; box-shadow: 0 22px 50px -30px rgba(234,106,46,0.35);">
    <img src="/portfolio/images/larc_team.webp" alt="Alessandro and teammate at LARC 2025"
         loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%; height:auto; display:block;" />
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>Engineering for Performance.</h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    Tracky runs on the ESP32-C6 (RISC-V core), executing an RTOS-like control loop that
    guarantees microsecond response times — making the robot hunt the line instead of just
    following it.
  </p>

  <div class="tech-grid" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100">
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">01</div>
      <h3>Inertial Recovery</h3>
      <p>If all 8 IR sensors hit white, Tracky pulls the derivative vector of its last known
      position and spins aggressively back — zero freeze, millisecond execution.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">02</div>
      <h3>Strat-Profiles</h3>
      <p>Physical DIP switches hot-swap between pre-calibrated PID profiles (Slow/Balanced/
      Aggressive/High-Damping) — no reflashing between heats, ever.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">03</div>
      <h3>BLE Auto-Healing</h3>
      <p>Python dashboard for live PID tuning over BLE. If the connection drops from arena
      interference, the robot continues autonomously at last known parameters.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div data-reveal style="border-radius:18px; overflow:hidden; margin: clamp(28px,4vh,48px) 0; box-shadow: 0 24px 60px -30px rgba(37,64,192,0.35);">
    <img src="/portfolio/images/robot_full.webp" alt="Tracky line follower robot — full hardware view"
         loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%; height:auto; display:block;" />
  </div>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  .pull-quote {
    border-left: 3px solid #ea6a2e;
    margin: clamp(32px,5vh,56px) 0;
    padding: clamp(16px,2.5vw,24px) clamp(20px,3vw,32px);
    background: #efe7d8;
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
  }
  .pull-quote p {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    font-size: clamp(17px, 1.9vw, 24px);
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: #211f1a;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .video-embed {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16/9;
    border-radius: 18px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 32px 80px -28px rgba(37,64,192,0.35);
    margin: clamp(20px,3vh,32px) 0 clamp(32px,5vh,56px);
    background: #211f1a;
  }
  .video-embed iframe {
    position: absolute; inset: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none;
  }
  .tech-num {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    font-size: 32px; color: #ea6a2e; line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
</style>
